  <main class="container">
    <section class="section">
      <h1>User Guide</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        This guide explains how a user would use the MealMate app prototype from setup through weekly shopping.
      </p>

      <div class="cards">
        <article class="card">
          <h2>Getting Started</h2>
          <ol class="steps">
            <li>Create an account (email or phone).</li>
            <li>Set household size and dietary preferences.</li>
            <li>Select budget goals (optional).</li>
          </ol>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h2>Create a Weekly Meal Plan</h2>
          <ol class="steps">
            <li>Choose meals from suggested recipes or add your own.</li>
            <li>Assign meals to days (Mon–Sun).</li>
            <li>Use “Swap” to replace meals quickly.</li>
          </ol>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
          <h2>Generate a Shopping List</h2>
          <ol class="steps">
            <li>Tap “Build List.”</li>
            <li>Review categories (produce, meat, dairy, etc.).</li>
            <li>Remove items you already have in your pantry.</li>
          </ol>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>Safety / Best Practices</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>Always check expiration dates and food storage guidelines.</li>
          <li>Use safe cooking temperatures for meats.</li>
          <li>Update pantry items after shopping to keep lists accurate.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="section">
        <h2>FAQ</h2>
        <details class="faq">
          <summary>Can I add my own recipes?</summary>
          <p>Yes. You can add custom meals and ingredients so the shopping list stays accurate.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq">
          <summary>Does MealMate work for meal prep?</summary>
          <p>Yes. You can plan bulk cooking and split portions across multiple days.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq">
          <summary>What if I’m on a tight budget?</summary>
          <p>The prototype includes a budget estimate concept and cheaper ingredient swap ideas.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>
